*'''''daor''''' - &quot;no&quot;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2014/5/8/high-valyrian-101-learn-and-pronounce-common-phrases MakingGameOfThrones]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''''dracarys''''' - (&quot;drah-KAH-ris&quot;)&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.dothraki.com/2012/06/ei-mahrazhith-drivoe/ David J. Peterson's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; The High Valyrian word for &quot;dragonfire&quot;. Daenerys says &quot;Dracarys&quot; to Drogon, the young [[Dragons|dragon]], to encourage him to breathe fire.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Ghost of Harrenhal]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; [[Daenerys Targaryen]] teaches her newly hatched dragons to breathe fire on command when she says ''dracarys'',â&euro;&lsaquo;â&euro;&lsaquo;â&euro;&lsaquo; burning [[Pyat Pree]] alive.&lt;ref name=&quot;E20&quot;&gt;&quot;[[Valar Morghulis]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; She also uses the command to make [[Drogon]] burn [[Kraznys mo Nakloz]] alive.&lt;ref&gt;[[And Now His Watch is Ended]]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''''kÄ&ldquo;li''''' - [[Cats|Cat]] (David J. Peterson's cat is named &quot;Keli&quot;, so he made it the noun for &quot;cat&quot; in High Valyrian).&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2014/5/8/interview-with-linguist-david-peterson MakingGameOfThrones.com]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''''kirimvose''''' - (or ''kirimvos'', for short; stress on the second &quot;i&quot; for both) &quot;thank you&quot;.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.dothraki.com/2012/12/merry-merry-goatmas/ David J. Peterson's blog], Dothraki.com, December 25h, 2012.&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''''kessa''''' - &quot;yes&quot;&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2014/5/8/high-valyrian-101-learn-and-pronounce-common-phrases MakingGameOfThrones]&lt;/ref&gt;
*'''''valar morghulis''''' - (val-are mor-goo-lis: &quot;valar&quot; uses short &quot;a&quot; as in &quot;valley&quot;, not long &quot;A&quot; as in &quot;vapor&quot;)&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.dothraki.com/2012/06/ei-mahrazhith-drivoe/ David J. Peterson's blog]&lt;/ref&gt; &quot;all men must die&quot;, in the sense of &quot;all men must (eventually) die (sooner or later)&quot;. Throughout the Valyrian-speaking world, it is used to indicate acceptance of a potentially unpleasant truth or assignment.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Walk of Punishment]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Second Sons (episode)|Second Sons]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; The word is also a common greeting, especially in [[Braavos]]&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;Â and particularly among the guild of assassins known as the [[Faceless Men]].&lt;ref name=&quot;E20&quot;/&gt; When used as a greeting, it is answered with the phrase &quot;'''''valar dohaeris'''''&quot;,&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Children]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; which translates to &quot;all men must serve&quot;.
*'''''zaldrizes''''' - [[Dragons]]&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.makinggameofthrones.com/production-diary/2014/5/8/interview-with-linguist-david-peterson MakingGameOfThrones.com]&lt;/ref&gt;
